Peaches Jackson https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Peaches_Jackson 0 Peaches Jackson (October 9, 1913 – February 23, 2002) is an American film actress. Her sister, Mary Ann Jackson also became a child actor, and appeared in many of the Little Rascals short films for Hal Roach. Peaches (Charlotte) stopped acting regularly in 1925, and later was a dancer in the film Dancing Lady (1933), and It's Great to Be Alive (1933).
